 Jose Mourinho is delighted after he was named as a coach of AS Roma on a three-year deal set to begin at the start of next season. The 58-year-old Portuguese coach struggled to convince his employers during his two-year stay with Spurs before he sacked in April after just 17 months in charge of the Premier League outfit. Mourinho took his social media handle to react after he was appointed as a head coach of AS Roma from next season with the Serie A club until 2024. Mourinho will be managing his tenth club after handling Benfica, União de Leiria, Porto, Chelsea, Inter Milan, Real Madrid, Manchester United, Tottenham Hotspurs. Post Views: 
